Colombian Stocks: Avianca Taca, Canacol, Pacific Rubiales

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-06-22T17:19:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/colombian-stocks-avianca-taca-canacol-pacific-rubiales.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 12:33 p.m. New York time.  The Colcap Index added 0.4 percent to 1,715.50. Bolsa de
Valores de  Colombia , operator of the country’s main securities
exchange, reported “inconsistencies” in data calculations for
the IGBC Index, according to an e-mailed statement.  Avianca Taca Holding SA (PFAVTA CB), owner of Colombia’s
biggest airline by sales, rose 0.2 percent to 5,220 pesos. It
signed a memorandum of understanding with Airbus to buy 51 new
A320 planes, the company said in an e-mailed statement today.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNE)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in  South America , rose 2 percent to
2,080 pesos. The company announced the start of its heavy oil
exploration drilling program on two contracts in southern
Colombia, according to a statement on the company’s website.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, rose 0.6 percent
to 49,400 pesos, adding to the biggest three-day gain since
April 7. Investors are betting the stock’s decline was overdone
after the company reported last month its first quarterly loss
in a year, said Camilo Rubiano, head of research at brokerage
Afin SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
